Of him he might be informed of all
those things which Methusalem had
heard and learned of Adam, and the
other Patriarches. Sem dieth after
the death of Abraham, in the 52. yeere
of Jaacob, which was 37. yeeres after
the death of Abraham, in the yeere
112. of Isaac his age : So that Jacob
the Patriarch might very well learne
all the true divinity of Sem himelfe,
even as hee had heard it of Methusa
lem, who was the third witnesse and
teacher from Adam. Furthermore,
Jaacob he Patriarch, delivered to his
children that which he received of
God, to teach to his posterity. In Me
sopotamia there is borne to Jacob his
sonne Levi, and to him againe is born
Bahad, which both sawe and heard
Jaacob. For Bahad lived no small
number of yeeres with his grandfa
ther Jaacob. For he is rehearsed in
the roll of them, which went with Ja
acob downe into Egypt: but Jaacob
lived 17. yeeres with his children in
Egypt. This Bahad is the grandfa
